### Manual verification script — VS Code "REST Client" extension.
### Run requests top to bottom. Update the @token variables from each response as you go
### (or use the extension's {{request.response.body.$.data.token}} chaining if preferred).

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### 1a. Signup an organiser
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Olivia Organiser",
  "email": "olivia@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "role": "organiser"
}

### 1b. Signup a regular user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Uma User",
  "email": "uma@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 1c. Login as seeded admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### --- paste tokens from the responses above into these variables ---
@organiserToken = PASTE_ORGANISER_TOKEN
@userToken = PASTE_USER_TOKEN
@adminToken = PASTE_ADMIN_TOKEN

### 2a. Create event as organiser (expect status: "pending")
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{organiserToken}}

{
  "title": "Verification Test Event",
  "description": "Created during manual verification",
  "category": "tech",
  "venueName": "Test Hall",
<<<<<<< HEAD
  "lat": 1.2936,
  "lng": 103.8580,
=======
  "lat": 37.7750,
  "lng": -122.4195,
>>>>>>> origin/main
  "startsAt": "2026-08-01T18:00:00",
  "endsAt": "2026-08-01T20:00:00",
  "capacity": 2
}

### 2b. Attempt to create event as plain user (expect 403)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "title": "Should Fail",
  "startsAt": "2026-08-01T18:00:00",
  "capacity": 10
}

### --- paste the new event's id from 2a's response ---
@eventId = PASTE_EVENT_ID

### 3a. Admin lists pending events
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/events/pending
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 3b. Admin approves the event
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/admin/events/{{eventId}}/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 3c. Public list now shows the approved event (pending ones excluded)
GET {{baseUrl}}/events

### 4. Map bounding box covering the event's lat/lng
