### 5a. Check availability
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/{{eventId}}/availability

### 5b. RSVP as user
POST {{baseUrl}}/rsvps
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "eventId": {{eventId}},
  "ticketCount": 1
}

### 5c. Repeat RSVP for same user/event (expect 409 ALREADY_RSVPD)
POST {{baseUrl}}/rsvps
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "eventId": {{eventId}},
  "ticketCount": 1
}

### 6. Concurrency smoke test: run this same request several times in parallel
### (e.g. via `autocannon`/a script hitting POST /api/rsvps with different user tokens)
### against an event with capacity smaller than total requested tickets.
### Confirm total confirmed ticket_count never exceeds capacity and excess requests get 409.

### 7a. User dashboard (expect the RSVP listed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 7b. Organiser rsvp-count (counts should match)
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/{{eventId}}/rsvp-count
Authorization: Bearer {{organiserToken}}

### 8a. Admin analytics
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/analytics
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### --- paste the user's id (from signup/login response) ---
@userId = PASTE_USER_ID

### 8b. Admin suspends the user
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/{{userId}}/suspend
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 8c. Attempt login as suspended user (expect 403 ACCOUNT_SUSPENDED)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "uma@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 9. Upload event banner as organiser (multipart) — use the REST Client's file picker
### or swap this for a curl command:
### curl -X POST {{baseUrl}}/events/{{eventId}}/banner \
###   -H "Authorization: Bearer <organiserToken>" \
###   -F "banner=@/path/to/image.jpg"
POST {{baseUrl}}/events/{{eventId}}/banner
Authorization: Bearer {{organiserToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="banner"; filename="test-banner.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-banner.jpg
--boundary--
